<task id="AIPU2-061" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extend SprkChatAgentFactory for Per-Turn Tool Injection via CapabilityRouter</title>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, routing</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-010, AIPU2-012, AIPU2-060</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    R1's SprkChatAgentFactory used a static ResolveTools method that returned the same tool list
    for every turn regardless of user intent. R2 requires per-turn tool injection driven by
    CapabilityRouter (AIPU2-010) and the model tier manifest (AIPU2-012). Extend
    SprkChatAgentFactory so that CreateAgentAsync accepts the current ChatTurnRequest, calls
    CapabilityRouter to select the appropriate tools, and injects them into the ISprkAgent before
    the turn executes. Middleware wrapping order (auth filter, rate limiter, safety pre-check)
    must be preserved around the per-turn resolved tool set.
  </prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET developer familiar with factory pattern, dependency injection, and the Azure OpenAI tool-use API.</role>
  <goal>
    Tools vary per turn based on user intent as determined by CapabilityRouter. The static
    ResolveTools method is replaced by manifest-driven resolution. Existing middleware wrapping
    order is preserved. Integration tests verify that different intents produce different tool
    sets injected into the agent.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read SprkChatAgentFactory.cs in full to map the current CreateAgentAsync signature and all call sites.</step>
    <step>Modify CreateAgentAsync signature to accept ChatTurnRequest (or relevant intent fields) alongside existing parameters.</step>
    <step>Inject ICapabilityRouter (AIPU2-010) into SprkChatAgentFactory constructor via DI.</step>
    <step>Replace the static ResolveTools call with CapabilityRouter.ResolveToolsAsync(turnRequest, modelTier) using the manifest from AIPU2-012.</step>
    <step>Pass the resolved IReadOnlyList&lt;AiTool&gt; into ISprkAgent.ExecuteTurnAsync per the interface defined in AIPU2-060.</step>
    <step>Preserve existing middleware wrapping order: auth filter wraps rate limiter wraps safety pre-check wraps agent call.</step>
    <step>Add per-turn tool injection into the Azure OpenAI call — tools must be set on the request object, not cached at factory creation time.</step>
    <step>Write integration tests: low-complexity intent resolves minimal tools; document-analysis intent resolves full tool set; capability_change SSE event emitted when tool set changes between turns.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Static ResolveTools method is removed or marked obsolete; all tool resolution goes through CapabilityRouter.</criterion>
    <criterion>Different chat intents produce different injected tool sets (verified by integration tests).</criterion>
    <criterion>Middleware wrapping order is unchanged — no auth or rate limit regression.</criterion>
    <criterion>capability_change SSE event is emitted when the resolved tool set differs from the previous turn.</criterion>
    <criterion>Factory compiles and all existing tests pass without modification to test intent.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
